Mirror Audit — Instruction

Purpose:
- Verify `test/` folder is fully mirrored by the scaffolder templates in `generate-file-structure.php`, identify missing/changed files, and produce actionable patches.
- `audit-sync.ps1` combines audit + auto-sync in one step.

Quick start (recommended):

```powershell
Push-Location "C:\xampp\htdocs\mlhuillier"
.\audit-sync.ps1          # Interactive: show preview, then apply on confirm
.\audit-sync.ps1 -Force    # Auto-apply all changes (CI / automation)
.\audit-sync.ps1 -DryRun   # Preview only, no file changes
Pop-Location
```

---

Mode reference:

  .\audit-sync.ps1 (default)
    1. Runs mirror-audit.ps1 to detect drift.
    2. Classifies files: text files become heredoc entries; binary files (png/jpg/etc.)
       are skipped with a warning.
    3. Shows a full preview (file list + first 4 content lines per entry).
    4. Prompts for confirmation before writing.
    5. Creates a timestamped backup in `audit/php-backups/`.
    6. Patches generate-file-structure.php. For existing template entries it replaces
       the heredoc; for missing entries it inserts them in alphabetical order.
    7. Validates: PHP syntax check, template dump, partial re-audit.

  -Force
    Skips the confirmation prompt. All changes are applied immediately.
    Best for CI pipelines and scripting.

  -DryRun
    Runs steps 1–3 only. Shows exactly what WOULD be changed without touching
    generate-file-structure.php.

What audit-sync.ps1 does NOT do:
- It does NOT modify `test/` (test/ is the authoritative source, never written to).
- Binary files are skipped because heredoc cannot safely encode them.
  If a new binary file appears in test/ that needs to be in the scaffold, add it
  to generate-file-structure.php manually (use base64 or use loadTemplatesFromDir
  fallback — test/ exists in the real project, so binary files are served from there).

Manual per-step workflow (for understanding / debugging):

  1) Run the mirror audit:

```powershell
Push-Location "C:\xampp\htdocs\mlhuillier"
.\mirror-audit.ps1
Pop-Location
```

  2) Review output files (all inside `audit/`):
  - `audit/test-files.txt`          — every file tracked in test/
  - `audit/scaffold_templates/`      — template dump from embedded PHP
  - `audit/audit-path-report.txt`    — MISSING-IN-SCAFFOLD / EXTRA-IN-SCAFFOLD
  - `audit/audit-diffs-list.txt`     — files that differ (content mismatch)
  - `audit/normal-diffs.txt`         — false-positive diffs (whitespace / placeholders)
  - `audit/error-diffs.txt`         — genuine content mismatches
  - `audit/audit-summary.txt`       — one-line summary

  3) Remediation guidance:
  - MISSING-IN-SCAFFOLD: add a new key in `generate-file-structure.php` with that
    relative path and the file content as a PHP heredoc entry (see existing format).
  - DIFF (in error-diffs.txt): inspect `audit/diffs/` then update the scaffolder
    template to match test/ (preferred: update test/, then re-sync).

  4) Validate by re-running: `php generate-file-structure.php create <name>`

  5) Optional — sync a live project (e.g. `del`):

```powershell
robocopy C:\xampp\htdocs\mlhuillier\test C:\xampp\htdocs\del /MIR /COPY:DAT /R:2 /W:1
```

---

Backup policy:
- `audit-sync.ps1` (non-dry-run) automatically backs up to
  `audit/php-backups/generate-file-structure.<timestamp>.bak` before writing.
- Restore: `Copy-Item audit/php-backups/generate-file-structure.<timestamp>.bak
  generate-file-structure.php`

Tips:
- Start with `-DryRun` to see what would change before applying.
- `audit/php-backups/` accumulates timestamped backups — safe to prune old ones.
- Keep only `audit/` for audit history. Clean it before a fresh run (auto-cleaned
  by mirror-audit.ps1 each time).

